  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nCreate contract transactions that fail have a transaction receipt which contains a non-null value for `contractAddress` receipt property. This is the case when no contract was actually created. This behaviour is inconsistent with the EVM which returns null if contract instantiation fails.\r\n\r\nThis behavior was noticed when a contract deployment failed because of out-of-gas rather than other constructor failures which have not been tested for the presence of this sympthom. \r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n`contractAddress` should be null in addition to the remaining symptoms of a failed contract creation, including `status = 0`, available revert error message etc.\r\n",
